CONTRIBUTING.md:1:# Contributing to Pinemeter
CONTRIBUTING.md:3:Thanks for helping improve Pinemeter. This project is a macOS menu bar app that reads local provider session/API state to show usage and quota information, so high-quality reports need to separate user-visible behavior from private credentials.
CONTRIBUTING.md:10:4. Do not paste Claude session keys, ChatGPT cookies, Gemini API keys, Cookie headers, request headers, or screenshots that expose account identifiers.
CONTRIBUTING.md:16:- Pinemeter version or commit SHA.
CONTRIBUTING.md:19:- Setup path used: browser import, manual credential entry, API key, source build via `xcodebuild`, upgrade from existing settings, or not configured.
CONTRIBUTING.md:23:- Logs or screenshots only after removing secrets, tokens, cookies, session identifiers, request headers, account identifiers, and private workspace names.
CONTRIBUTING.md:37:- Treat provider credentials, cookies, tokens, and headers as secret material. Do not log or persist raw values outside their intended secure storage boundary.
